      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "an4.228:1.1",
          "pli": "… pe … Diṭṭhe adiṭṭhavādī hoti, sute asutavādī hoti, mute amutavādī hoti, viññāte aviññātavādī hoti … pe … diṭṭhe diṭṭhavādī hoti, sute sutavādī hoti, mute mutavādī hoti, viññāte viññātavādī hoti … pe …. ",
          "en": "“A foolish person … makes much bad karma. … They say they haven’t seen, heard, thought, or known something, but they have. … An astute person … makes much merit. … They say they’ve seen, heard, thought, or known something, and they have. …” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.228:1.2",
          "pli": "Aṭṭhamaṃ. ",
